<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1957,2092]" pageId="7" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis box="[136,236,1957,1983]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="274">Colonies</emphasis>
on PDA covered half the 
<quantity box="[539,597,1958,1984]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="274" unit="cm" value="9.0">9 cm</quantity>
plate in 7 days at 28–30 
<superScript attach="right" box="[893,901,1957,1971]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="274">0</superScript>
C, grey with a white margin, reverse black with a white margin, circular, margin undulate, appearance powdery, mycelia white and raised, melanized hyphae with brownish exudates (
<figureCitation box="[362,478,2029,2056]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1856,1878]" captionTargetBox="[163,1416,207,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[151,1436,190,1832]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Colony morphology (upper surface and lower surface) and microscopic features (conidia and conidiophore) respectively of fungal pure cultures from Oryza sativa on PDA after 10 days at 28–30 0C; a–c Rhizopus oryzae, d–f Bipolaris sivanesaniana, g–i Daldinia eschscholtzii and j–l Orbilia foliicola." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886370" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886370/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="274">Figure 3h</figureCitation>
.). 
<emphasis box="[504,659,2029,2055]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="274">Conidiophore</emphasis>
0.8–2 μm (x̄=1.5) in length and 0.7–1.5 μm (x̄=1.2) in width, septate, thin-walled, hyaline, black exudates, irregular branching (
<figureCitation box="[784,891,2065,2092]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1856,1878]" captionTargetBox="[163,1416,207,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[151,1436,190,1832]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Colony morphology (upper surface and lower surface) and microscopic features (conidia and conidiophore) respectively of fungal pure cultures from Oryza sativa on PDA after 10 days at 28–30 0C; a–c Rhizopus oryzae, d–f Bipolaris sivanesaniana, g–i Daldinia eschscholtzii and j–l Orbilia foliicola." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886370" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886370/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="274">Figure 3i</figureCitation>
.).
</paragraph>
